# Reap idle per-cell test workdirs created by the CI workflows. Each
# cell bind-mounts a unique subdir under here (host path embeds
# github.run_id + strategy.job-index; see .github/workflows/test.yml).
# Cleanup mechanics: `e` cleans files older than the Age field, then
# recursively removes empty subdirs that are also old enough -- so a
# completed/crashed cell's tree gets eaten once its contents are >1d
# stale. The scratch dir itself is the rule target and stays. Age=1d
# is comfortably beyond the harness's 1500s timeout, so a live cell
# can't be reaped mid-run.
#
# The /mnt/scratch/qemu/_sentinels d+e rules are intentionally absent
# during the act_runner -> github_runner transition: both runners would
# otherwise declare them, and systemd-tmpfiles' validate refuses the
# canonicalization of /mnt/scratch/qemu/_sentinels (owned by root)
# starting from /mnt/scratch/qemu (owned by act_runner). act_runner's
# tmpfiles.conf owns those rules until the cutover commit, which moves
# them here as act_runner.conf is deleted.
#
# Type Path                                       Mode UID GID Age  Argument
e      /mnt/scratch/github_runner/scratch         -    -   -   1d

# actions/runner hardcodes `-v /var/run/docker.sock:/var/run/docker.sock`
# on every `docker create` so workflow steps can talk to a Docker daemon
# from inside their job container (GitHub-hosted-runner parity). Lab has
# no dockerd; point /var/run/docker.sock at github_runner's rootless
# podman socket, whose docker-compat API handles every verb a workflow
# is likely to call. Symlink because /var/run is tmpfs -- systemd-
# tmpfiles-setup.service re-runs the L rule at boot. The target uid
# comes from the github_runner user record so the path tracks whatever
# uid useradd allocated.
L      /var/run/docker.sock                                -    -   -   -    /run/user/{{ github_runner_user.uid }}/podman/podman.sock
